Full data reset: wipe endpoints + webhook delete fix

Changes:
1. server/api/bootstrapRoute.ts — adds POST /api/setup/full-reset
   Deletes event_fights, fight_history, news_articles, data_pipeline
   (children first), then events and fighters. Returns row counts.
   Protected by DATA_ENGINE_API_KEY. User accounts untouched.

2. server/api/webhooks/dataEngineWebhook.ts — skip schema validation
   for delete actions (only sourceId is needed). Previously all fields
   were validated even for deletes, blocking any webhook delete calls.
   Also validates sourceId is present when actionType === 'delete'.

3. shared/sync-schemas.ts — imageUrl is now optional/nullable on
   syncFighterSchema (was incorrectly required).

4. server/services/dataEngineService.ts — normalizeFighterData defaults
   imageUrl to '' when omitted (image_url column is NOT NULL in DB).

After this deploy: call POST /api/setup/full-reset on production
to complete the wipe (auth header: x-data-engine-api-key).
